<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="3970" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[418,940,886,943]" box="[604,719,919,943]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
(
<figureCitation box="[611,710,919,943]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 7</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,230,1000,1024]" box="[125,230,1000,1024]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,230,1000,1024]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,1172,1048,1169]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
Secondary process of paramere larger than primary process, with a spine-shaped projection apically (
<figureCitation box="[229,351,1080,1104]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 7C</figureCitation>
); branch of aedeagal basal bridge strong, tripartite (
<figureCitation box="[959,1081,1080,1104]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 7C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,1172,1048,1169]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
Some characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen, 2005" authorityName="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[599,732,1113,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[599,732,1113,1137]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">P. uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[746,844,1113,1137]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are not referred to in the following description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,245,1226,1250]" box="[125,245,1226,1250]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,245,1226,1250]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,1173,1274,1330]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,194,1274,1298]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Head.</emphasis>
Frons brown. Arista basally with dorsal branches. Face brown. Gena black. Postgena brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,969,1371,1395]" box="[125,969,1371,1395]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,214,1371,1395]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pleura nearly entirely black. Anepisternum with several setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,937,1436,1460]" box="[125,937,1436,1460]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,183,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Legs.</emphasis>
Mid tibia subapically with two longer setae on anterior surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,1172,1501,1556]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,236,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Abdominal third and fifth tergites with medially and sublaterally interrupted, broad, brown-black bands along posterior margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,1172,1597,1685]" lastBlockId="20.[138,1185,1095,1216]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="3969" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,316,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium lacking pubescence anteroventrally, with eight setae near dorsal to posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[461,583,1629,1653]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 7A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with pubescence and dense setae, and about 15–17 apically round prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[606,728,1661,1685]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 7A</figureCitation>
). Vertical process of gonopod slightly narrowed and sclerotized apically (
<figureCitation box="[538,659,1095,1119]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="3969">Figure 7C</figureCitation>
). Paramere submedially pubescent and much expanded, with two processes apically: primary process with one sensillum and three small teeth apically (
<figureCitation box="[321,443,1159,1183]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="3969">Figure 7C</figureCitation>
); aedeagal median rod asymmetrically expanded subapically (
<figureCitation box="[146,268,1192,1216]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[138,198,975,994]" captionTargetBox="[139,1183,134,938]" captionTargetId="figure-164@20.[138,1186,133,939]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. Phortica latipenis Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221190/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="3969">Figure 7C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
